Well, I'm enjoying it immensely.  Not a single game has grabbed like this since EQ did four years ago.  <br>
<br>
There are issues, characters skating, clothing not appearing till you get right up on them, but things like that will get ironed out in time.  Considering the other launches I've played on, this is really, really smooth.  I like that the characters don't look cartoony.  There really is variety with the faces...easier to see in creation when you hit that /up button to zoom in.  And then on top of the faces, you can change face styles.<br>
<br>
<br>
Still wish the wood elf skin wasn't morning-piss yellow, but I'm really falling for this game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhatha>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Animist of Shar Vahl<br>Swiftclaw wants fish!<br></span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/03 12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2170.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Horizons...</span><hr size=1> Don't you just love finding random things in the middle of nowhere and going, &quot;What the hell happened here?!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/bones.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
To give you some idea, that's about as long as five ancient dragons, maybe more.  I wanna know what it is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Clerics:  I got my first taste of being cleric in a group today.. heck of a lot more to do than in eq.. closer to a D&amp;D cleric.  In general, tank pulled a critter, I'd target them, use Protective ability (forget the exact name), and hit assist to get the foe.  Protective ability redirects 85% of attacks aimed at the targget to you instead, for 30 seconds.  Once I'm on the mob, I hit my avoidance ability to help dodge the protected attacks, and attemp to slow the foe.  Yes, clerics slow.  The one I have currently modifies delay by 150%.<br>
<br>
After all this, in the first couple seconds, everyone is crowding around the enemy hacking them to bits.  We were fighting things five levels above our highest player, so I didn't really have time to use combat abilities, I just grabbed the tank, gave them a big heal, myself a small heal, then a group heal, saving the instant heal ability (think mini lay on hands) for tight situations.  After that, my heals are exhausted for a few seconds, so if the enemy isn't dead yet I'd go back and hit them with Bash I, an extra damage attack for crushing weapons, or magic hammer, short range attack.  One nice thing about combat is that once you turn autoattack on (or a repeating spell, for casters) you can target other players to cast whatever you want, or mix in your combat abilities, and you'll still be attacking your target.  No switching to the wrong one by mistake (with auto, anyway), and in between heals you're still smacking em up.<br>
<br>
So clerics have a lot to do in a group, without considering stances etc. (more on that some other time).  How about solo?  Well, I can't speak for a cleric from day one, I started as a scout and multiclassed, giving me the scout's evasion, armor use, crushing skill, etc until cleric levels passed some of it up, a load more hp, and so on.  However, I will say that as long as you obtain key spells and have a decent weapon, you'll be ablo to solo well up to your level or slightly below.  You certainly won't be kiting things many levels above you like some classes, but you can make a good amount of xp and have virtually no downtime.  Never using mana is a good thing.  I'd think, though, that a duo at least would be far more effective, with either a high damage character and you tanking/protecting them, or a tank with both of you getting in there and you healing.<br>
<br>
And finally, buffs: clerics are the best buffing class I've come across thus far, by FAR.  Each character has one &quot;gift&quot; buff slot, and then the rest of their bar.  Gifts are your 2 hour buffs, starting from level 1.  There's one for each stat, for armor, for haste, and fr movement speed, starting at level 1 and with upgrades later.  Also, you have increase XXX buffs.  You can have one of these on for physical stats (str, dex, health), and one for magical stats (power, focus).  And then there's everything else.<br>
<br>
Oh, yeah, and the resurrection animation kicks so much ass. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://darklance.freewebspace.com/custom.html">Rhatha Sha`Naya and Swiftclaw</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
